<p>It is worth noting that even though deals 1 and 2 had a similar healthy initial arbitrage or net interest margin (portfolio weighted average spread net of cost of funding), they ended up experiencing completely different IRRs. This suggests that having a good initial arbitrage metric is not always a reliable indicator of a deal&#8217;s future performance.</p>
